arStrings.szText: Holding this camp is a lost cause. We would be better off preserving Zarbinzet, not being butchered by cultists and rotting in the bog.
Tired. Frustrated. ERENDER cares a lot about his men and is upset that they are dying under his watch.
Weâ€™ve retrieved most of the dead, but some personal effects were missing: prayer amulets. Those cultists pillaged the bodies and wear them now, mocking our crusade.
More heated than the previous line. He views the cultists that killed his men to be scum.
I want them returned and the thieves eradicated, but the remaining garrison is my priority. Please help with this.
